race.comment: CAPSITY (6) lifted strongly to score last time with a bit in hand at Scone, making it two in a row. Is a progressive filly with more to offer and is drawn to get all the favours. Hat-trick is on the cards. MASTER GEE (7) doesn't win out of turn but ran a strong race last time out when again running second. Not a great deal tougher this time and gets in well with the claimer engaged. Can go one better. MUM KNOWS (12) bounced straight to the front first-up at Coffs Harbour and never got reeled in. Tougher now but strips fitter and gets in low at the weights. Could steal it again if left alone. POWERSTONE (8) also resumed a winner at the latest when fending off her rivals to win by a head. Carries more weight this time but is sure to have come on from that and deserves following up. MISS INDI (11) is still searching for her second win but is a consistent mare worth keeping safe in the numbers.
